# Amdani Xpress Platform Rules

You are working on Amdani Xpress — a cross-border import platform for Bangladesh.
Users source products from Taobao/1688/Alibaba and get them delivered door-to-door in BD.

## Context Files (READ FIRST)
- `.ai/CONTEXT.md` — Project overview and team info
- `.ai/RULES.md` — Detailed coding rules
- `.ai/MEMORY.md` — Decision log
- `.ai/TASKS.md` — Task tracking

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15+ (App Router) — Web
- React Native (Expo) — Mobile
- Supabase (PostgreSQL) — Database
- Prisma — ORM
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui — Styling
- SSLCommerz — Payments
- Turborepo + pnpm — Monorepo

## Style & Conventions
- TypeScript everywhere. No `any`.
- Server components by default (Next.js App Router)
- Tailwind classes for styling
- Zod for validation
- React Query for server state
- Prisma for all database queries
- `'use client'` only when necessary

## File Structure
```
apps/web/       — Next.js public website + customer portal
apps/mobile/    — Expo React Native app
apps/admin/     — Admin dashboard
packages/shared/ — Shared types, constants, utils
packages/api/    — API service layer
packages/database/ — Prisma schema & migrations
packages/ui/     — Shared UI components (shadcn)
services/        — External integrations
```

## Critical Rules
1. Never commit secrets. Use `.env` file.
2. Always update `.ai/MEMORY.md` for significant decisions.
3. Always update `.ai/TASKS.md` when completing tasks.
4. Support Bengali (bn) + English (en) UI.
5. Mobile-first responsive design.
6. All times in UTC unless displaying to user.
7. Currency: store in CNY, display in BDT.
